added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: The Date
added.description: When Chef is happy he orders pizza for the kids, this gives Owen & Jude the idea to create a fake secret admirer for Chef.

added.title: Venthalla
added.description: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

added.title: Duck Duck Juice
added.description: After daring each other to drink Chef's Pegasus Rainbow Latte, Izzy and Jude are jacked up like crazy and Duncan and Courtney take a road trip to try and replace the drink before Chef finds out it's gone.

added.title: Cluckwork Orange
added.description: After befriending a chicken with a bad attitude at a petting zoo, Jude is followed back to school by the chicken. He defends the bad bird's behavior until he can defend it no longer.

added.title: Free Chili
added.description: When Owen hides a walkie-talkie inside his chili dog, Harold believes it's an alien here to destroy Earth.

added.title: Aquarium for a Dream
added.description: Gwen tries to convince Chef to tell the class the truth about their pet goldfish.

added.title: Cuttin' Corners
added.description: Duncan, Leshawna and Jude all want corner pieces of Izzy's Birthday Cake… But are they prepared to go to any length to get one?

added.title: The Forbidden Isle/New World Orders
added.description: The Forbidden Isle: The AO travel to a remote island in search of a Core Cell, but instead they find the Bakugan known as Kelion, which soon bonds with Dan./New World Orders: The AO discover a small group of kids and Bakugan being used as laborers against their will, but freeing them is only half the problem.

added.title: In the Wild/Call Me Old Brakken
added.description: In the Wild: The AO are invited to a video-stars conference, but when the chartered jet goes down, the AO must give over to their wild sides to survive!/Call Me Old Brakken: Lord Brakken is the ultimate AO super-fan, but his zeal takes a dark turn when he looks to prove that he is their superior in battle.

added.title: Hide Matrix and Seek/Or Forever Hold Your Peace
added.description: Hide Matrix and Seek: The AO go undercover to try and pass as citizens of Lord Brakken, but quickly discover that even minor celebrity makes anonymity impossible./Or Forever Hold Your Peace: The AO seek to rescue Lia from an arranged marriage with Lord Brakken only to discover she just made a major discovery for the Bakugan!

added.title: Two Sides of the Coin/The Race for Gold
added.description: Two Sides of the Coin: The AO and Magnus take parallel tracks to retrieve the same piece of data, one that promises a breakthrough in the Bakugan phenomenon./The Race for Gold: When the AO seek out a mythical, lost Bakugan, they get more than they bargained for when Magnus is on the trail of this new discovery, too.

added.title: Seek and Hide/Family First
added.description: Seek and Hide: Sent to investigate a Japanese island by Benton Dusk, the AO discover a hidden facility conducting experiments that affect The Hide./Family First: Trapped by his father, Shun is forced to battle his own friends, revealing dark secrets about the Kazami family and Masato's experiments.

added.title: A Door Closes, A Door Opens/Kazami's Gambit
added.description: A Door Closes, A Door Opens: Shun must stand up to his father, expose his cousin and protect his friends before Masato destroys everyone on Ichiro's island!/Kazami's Gambit: When Magnus looks to steal the Dimensional Doorway, Shun and Ichiro must make peace while the AO stop the Doorway from destroying them all.

added.title: Chile libre
added.description: Cuando Owen oculta un walkie talky dentro de su perro con chile, Harold cree que es un alienígena que vino a destruir la tierra.

added.title: Manzana esta en Problemas
added.description: Bistec con Queso, malhumorado, desafía a Manzana a una pelea. De ese modo, Manzana puede embarcarse con Cebollín en una misión para encontrar el origen del malhumor de Bistec con Queso.

added.title: La pecera de los suenos
added.description: Gwen trata de convencer a Chef de que le diga a la clase la verdad sobre su pececito dorado.

added.title: 4 a 1
added.description: El temor de Cebollín a las multitudes amenaza el éxito de su equipo de baloncesto.

added.title: Hot Dog estrena su pelicula
added.description: Cuando unos guardias de seguridad muy serios los echan del estreno de la nueva película de su amigo Hot Dog, Manzana y Cebollín se preparan para pelear.

added.title: Fabrica de germenes
added.description: Después de ver a Leshawna disfrutar de un día enferma en casa con helado y TV, Duncan convence a los otros chicos de que traten de enfermarse.

added.title: Ventila-hala
added.description: Chef le confisca la mega-bola a Owen y la guarda en su oficina. Duncan, viendo una oportunidad para conseguir ayuda escapando de la guardaería, lidera un equipo de fuga por los conductos del aire acondicionado para recuperarla.

added.title: Una Nueva Vida
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín abandonan sus hogares y se mudan a la ciudad, donde se conocen por primera vez.

added.title: Jugo arcoiris
added.description: Después de desafiarse unos a otros a tomar el Latte de Pegaso de Chef, Izzy y Jude están llenos de energía y Duncan y Courtney hacen un viaje por carretera para tratar de reemplazar la bebida antes de que Chef descubra que desapareció.

added.title: El Equipo Perfecto
added.description: A Cebollín le preocupa que su relación con Manzana corra peligro cuando un gato callejero entra en su vida.

added.title: Propinas
added.description: Luego de destruir por accidente el boleto de Falafel para un concierto, Manzana y Cebollín deben descubrir un modo de evitar la furia de Falafel.

added.title: El pollo maniaco
added.description: Después de hacerse amigo de un pollo con mala actitud en un zoológico de contacto, este lo sigue de regreso a la escuela. Él defiende la mala conducta del ave hasta que ya no puede seguir haciéndolo.

added.title: El dia divertido de Falafel
added.description: Cuando Falafel decide empacar sus cosas e ir a la ciudad, Manzana y Cebollín deben convencerlo de quedarse.

added.title: La cita
added.description: Cuando Chef está feliz ordena pizza para los niños. Esto le da a Owen & Jude la idea de crear una falsa admiradora secreta para Chef.
